M. P. MOSELEY, Appellant, v. C. D. CALBECK, Deputy Commissioner, et al., Appellees. No. 22457. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. April 19, 1966. Herman Wright, Houston, Tex., for appellant. Bryan F. Williams, Jr., Galveston, Tex., Florence Wagman Roisman, Alan S. Rosenthal, Attys., Dept, of Justice, Washington, D. C., John W. Douglas, Asst. Atty. Gen., Woodrow B. Seals, U. S. Atty., Washington, D. C., for ap-pellees.

Before TUTTLE, Chief Judge, and JONES and WATERMAN* Circuit Judges.

Of the Second Circuit, sitting by designation.

 PER CURIAM:

We have carefully considered the entire record before the Commissioner and conclude that no errors were committed by the Commissioner in the application of the appropriate standards. Moreover, the fact determinations were amply supported by the evidence before the Commissioner.

The judgment is affirmed.
